  "rationale": "The competitor price of $149.99 is below the vendor MAP of $169.99, so a direct match would violate a known pricing control. At $169.99 versus unit cost of $118.00, the item still retains positive unit margin before considering attachment economics, but pricing below MAP is not permitted. Counterfeit concern is material because 31 percent of recent returns cite authenticity concerns in competitor reviews, which weakens the case for treating the marketplace listing as a valid comparable offer. Given the severe downside and hard case type, the bounded action is to refuse the below-MAP match and only consider MAP-compliant pricing action.",
